webpackJsonp([0x81b8806e4260],{339:function(A,a){A.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"AMALIA VITI"}},about:{html:'<p>I like to make things. I am fascinated with the way things work and have been a tinkerer for as long as I can remember. That cool place where technology, design, and creativity intersect is where I like to spend most of my time.</p>\n<p>I most recently worked as a <strong>full-stack engineer</strong> at <strong><a href="http://www.beme.com">Beme</a></strong>.</p>\n<p>If you\'d like to get in touch, <a href="mailto:amalia.viti@gmail.com" target="_blank">email me</a>.</p>'},projects:{edges:[{node:{id:"/Users/amaliaviti/projects/aamaliaa.github.io-new/content/projects/mirror/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I created a smart mirror for my apartment. This display hangs in my apartment and displays information useful at a glance--current time and date, the day\'s weather forecast, personal calendar events, nearby subway times, Citibike dock availability, and daily scheduled reminders.</p>\n<h4>V1 (2016)</h4>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-8576a.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Mirror V1"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-893a4.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-bbf57.jpg 200w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-260b8.jpg 400w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-893a4.jpg 800w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-25965.jpg 1200w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-e54c8.jpg 1600w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-7c0ed.jpg 2400w,\n/static/mirror-v1-a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1-8576a.jpg 3024w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>I created the first non-interactive prototype using an old Dell netbook, plastic two-way mirror, and a custom-made wooden frame.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-8576a.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Mirror V1 Inside"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-893a4.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-bbf57.jpg 200w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-260b8.jpg 400w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-893a4.jpg 800w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-25965.jpg 1200w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-e54c8.jpg 1600w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-7c0ed.jpg 2400w,\n/static/mirror-v1-inside-0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c-8576a.jpg 3024w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The software ran a Node.js server on the backend and a React.js front-end. Glancing at it while getting ready quickly became a part of my morning routine.</p>\n<h4>V2 (2018)</h4>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-8576a.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Mirror V2"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-893a4.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-bbf57.jpg 200w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-260b8.jpg 400w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-893a4.jpg 800w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-25965.jpg 1200w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-e54c8.jpg 1600w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-7c0ed.jpg 2400w,\n/static/mirror-v2-435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6-8576a.jpg 3024w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The newest version is interactive via voice recognition (albeit a very crude version of it, currently). It is an Electron app running on Raspberry Pi that also utilizes React.js for the UI and has a much larger 1080p display.</p>',fields:{slug:"/projects/mirror/"},frontmatter:{title:"Mirror",created:"2018",path:null,description:"My mirror is smarter than yours.",featured:!0}}},{node:{id:"/Users/amaliaviti/projects/aamaliaa.github.io-new/content/projects/atlas/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I led development of <a href="http://atlas.qz.com">Atlas</a>, Quartz\'s <a href="http://qz.com/434425/atlas-the-new-home-for-charts-and-data/">platform for discovering and sharing charts</a>.</p>\n<p>The site is built with React and Node.js and is <a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/04/21/react-to-the-future-with-isomorphic-apps">isomorphic</a>. Quite the buzzword, but it means that the same React javascript components are rendered on the server-side as well as the client-side, which proved to be a huge convenience in terms of development. In the past, I\'ve worked on projects that either forego server-side rendering of content completely (and rely solely on the API) and others that use two separate templates to render the same exact markup (PHP and underscore.js, for example). I introduced the team to Node.js and React + Flux while developing the site.</p>',fields:{slug:"/projects/atlas/"},frontmatter:{title:"Atlas",created:"2015",path:null,description:"A platform for discovering and sharing charts.",featured:!0}}},{node:{id:"/Users/amaliaviti/projects/aamaliaa.github.io-new/content/projects/mta-gtfs.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I needed real-time subway data for a project I was working on so I created a Node.js library to access the real-time MTA subway train schedule API.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/mta-gtfs"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/mta-gtfs.svg?style=flat-square" alt="npm"></a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/mta-gtfs"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/dt/mta-gtfs.svg?style=flat-square" alt="npm"></a></p>\n<p>It powers a subway widget in the current version of <a href="/projects/mirror">Mirror</a> and has been downloaded ~2k times via npm.</p>',fields:{slug:"/projects/mta-gtfs/"},frontmatter:{title:"MTA GTFS npm package",created:"2015",path:null,description:"A Node.js NYC MTA API library.",featured:!0}}},{node:{id:"/Users/amaliaviti/projects/aamaliaa.github.io-new/content/projects/weather-cloud/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>WeatherCloud is an internet-powered hanging lamp that brings the weather inside your home. Inspired by an Etsy cloud lamp and the original prototype of <a href="http://www.richardclarkson.com/cloud/">The Cloud</a> by Richard Clarkson (originally spied at SVA\'s Products of Design lab), I decided to design my own lamp that utilized live weather data to inform its owner of the current weather in their neighborhood. It currently lives happily in my apartment.</p>\n<p>Its electronic guts are comprised of a <a href="https://store.particle.io/?product=particle-photon">Particle Photon</a> (like an Arduino) and a string of LEDs. It uses <a href="https://developer.forecast.io/">Dark Sky Forecast API</a> for its live data.</p>\n<p>There are different light patterns to match each weather pattern. Here are a couple of examples:</p>\n<p>When it\'s a clear day, the cloud glows a warm red-orange...</p>\n<blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-version="4" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:8px;"> <div style=" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;"> <div style=" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;"></div></div><p style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"><a href="https://instagram.com/p/t7pqqhM1aE/" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_top">A video posted by aamaliaa (@aamaliaa)</a> on <time style=" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;" datetime="2014-10-09T12:39:02+00:00">Oct 9, 2014 at 5:39am PDT</time></p></div></blockquote>\n<p>and when it\'s raining, naturally, lightning flashes fill the cloud...</p>\n<blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-version="4" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:8px;"> <div style=" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;"> <div style=" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;"></div></div><p style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"><a href="https://instagram.com/p/3NOCSBM1T7/" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_top">A video posted by aamaliaa (@aamaliaa)</a> on <time style=" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;" datetime="2015-05-28T01:06:28+00:00">May 27, 2015 at 6:06pm PDT</time></p></div></blockquote>\n<script async defer src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script>',fields:{slug:"/projects/weather-cloud/"},frontmatter:{title:"WeatherCloud",created:"2014",path:null,description:"An internet-connected lamp that shows the weather.",featured:!0}}}]}},pathContext:{}}}});
